  "texts": [
    "In our study, we utilized topic modeling to search for and identify dominant themes from AI-related news headlines.",
    "Our methodology involved the use of BERTopic (76), a method that employs BERT(Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers) word embeddings to derive semantically rich sentence embeddings from documents.",
    "(77) We preferred BERTopic(76) to Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) because of its superior capability in capturing the contextual meanings of words, a strength supported by previous studies showing BERTopic's effectiveness over LDA and Top2Vec in topic detection from online discussions.",
    "(78; 79)BERTopic(76) combines advanced NLP techniques for topic modeling, integrating BERT embeddings with dimensionality reduction and clustering algorithms to identify text corpus topics.We began by converting our text data into embeddings using Sentence Transformers, specifically designed for creating sentence embeddings, thus turning sentences into high-dimensional vectors.",
    "To manage the embeddings' high dimensionality, we applied Uniform Manifold Approximation and Projection (UMAP) for dimensionality reduction, which maintains the data's local and global structure for easier visualization and clustering."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}